//
// File: zannastudio/src/ui/scene_editor_2d.zia
// Purpose: Visual tileset/tile/layer/object editor for canonical Game2D scene
//          files.
// Key invariants:
//   - Zanna.Game2D.SceneDocument is the only editable scene source of truth.
//   - Every accepted mutation immediately refreshes Document.content as
//     canonical JSON, so normal save/session/recovery paths remain authoritative.
//   - One paint or object-drag gesture creates one gap-free history snapshot.
//   - Compact windows show canvas or inspector at full width, never two slivers.
//   - Raster work is bounded even for malformed or resource-limit-sized maps.
//   - Layer images resolve through bounded preview caches; broken references
//     never invalidate or rewrite authored scene JSON.
//   - Multi-object property, layout, nudge, and selection commands commit once
//     or restore the complete prior selection/content; inspector inputs never
//     own scene keys.
// Ownership/Lifetime:
//   - Main owns one controller; WorkbenchShell owns its persistent host widgets.
//   - The controller borrows the active Document and recreates its model on
//     document/content changes.
// Links: zannastudio/src/core/document.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_clipboard.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_layout_2d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_tileset_2d.zia,
//        zannastudio/src/ui/scene_tileset_inspector_2d.zia,
//        docs/zannalib/game/scene.md,
//        docs/adr/0155-scene-object-authoring-metadata-and-duplication.md,
//        docs/adr/0156-listbox-selected-row-data.md
//
//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

